data.title: Foreign Minister Baerbock welcomes Germany joining the United Nations Command on the Korean Peninsula
data.meta_description: Today Germany joined the United Nations Command that has been monitoring the enforcement of the Armistice Agreement in the demilitarised Zone between North and South Korea since 1953. Germany’s…
data.text:
Today Germany joined the United Nations Command that has been monitoring the enforcement of the Armistice Agreement in the demilitarised Zone between North and South Korea since 1953. Germany’s application to join was successful.

Foreign Minister Annalena Baerbock issued the following statement today (2 August):
